The paper focuses on accelerating the performance of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) through a software approach that reorganizes the computation of deconvolutional layers. This is a common problem in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) research, which suggests that cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel method for accelerating GANs that does not require hardware modifications, which could also fall under the categories of cs.AI and cs.NE. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed method on representative CNN accelerators, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.AR.
